t%20just%20domestic%20flights%20that%20have%20gotten%20more%20affordable.%20Keyes%20said%20international%20inflation-adjusted%20airfares%20for%20US%20passengers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fgraph%2F%3Fg%3D1oxmN%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20generally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fgraph%2F%3Fg%3D1oxn3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efallen%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrustrations%20over%20flying%20costs%20could%20be%20among%20the%20reasons%20the%20share%20of%20Americans%20with%20a%20negative%20opinion%20of%20the%20airline%20industry%20is%20at%20the%20highest%20level%20since%202011%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Gallup%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F1579%2Fairlines.aspx%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%25202023%252C%252035%2525%2520of%2520Americans%2Chad%2520an%2520overall%2520negative%2520view.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20over%201%2C000%20US%20adults%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Econducted%20last%20August.%20The%20federal%20government%20seems%20to%20have%20taken%20notice.%20In%20January%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20blocked%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fspirit-airlines-stock-price-jet-blue-merger-judge-doj-antitrust-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJetBlue-Spirit%20Airlines%20merger%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20Biden%20Administration%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20impact%20it%20would%20have%20on%20flight%20prices.%20In%20April%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairlines-sue-biden-administration-dot-fee-transparency-baggage-change-seat-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20a%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20said%20would%20protect%20consumers%20from%20%26quot%3Bsurprise%20junk%20fees%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20the%20costs%20of%20additional%20baggage%20and%20reservation%20changes%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20save%20fliers%20over%20%24500%20million%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20any%20frustrations%20about%20airfare%20prices%20haven't%20stopped%20many%20Americans%20from%20flying.%20When%20pandemic%20restrictions%20eased%2C%20Americans%20unleashed%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendants-and-pilots-anxiously-gear-up-for-summer-travel-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epent-up%20travel%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20airline%20industry.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnd%20that%20momentum%20has%20continued%3A%20on%20May%2024%2C%20TSA%20officers%20screened%20nearly%20three%20million%20passengers%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F05%2F25%2Fbusiness%2Ftsa-travel-record-memorial-day-weekend%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%3C%2Fa%3E%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20overall%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCUSR0000SETG01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecline%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20actual%20airfare%20prices%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years%20suggests%20passenger%20demand%20%26quot%3Bseems%20to%20have%20subsided%26quot%3B%20a%20bit%2C%20Kerry%20Tan%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20Loyola%20University%20Maryland%2C%20told%20BI%20via%20email.%20He%20said%20this%20suggests%20demand%20could%20be%20normalizing%20and%20that%20some%20Americans%20balked%20at%202022's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-airfare-is-so-high-fuel-prices-demand-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euptick%20in%20flight%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20tickets%20remained%20more%20affordable%20than%20pre-pandemic%20levels%20when%20adjusted%20for%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20forward%2C%20airlines%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20impacted%20by%20Americans'%20perception%20of%20flight%20prices.%20To%20the%20extent%20this%20perception%20influences%20Americans'%20broader%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresident-joe-biden-donald-trump-economy-voters-polls-jobs-inflation-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeelings%20about%20inflation%20and%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20could%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20presidential%20election%20this%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20airline%20industry%20experts%20to%20learn%20why%20inflation-adjusted%20airfares%20have%20fallen%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why%20some%20Americans%20don't%20seem%20to%20have%20noticed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228c5e1c74-c9f1-4f2a-a611-1ce3f2f43bd4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20flights%20have%20become%20more%20affordable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAirline%20industry%20experts%20told%20BI%20that%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20factors%20driving%20down%20inflation-adjusted%20airfares%20is%20the%20rise%20of%20lower-cost%2C%20budget%20airlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20United%2C%20American%2C%20and%20Delta%20flights%20accounted%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airlines.org%2Fdataset%2Fa4a-presentation-industry-review-and-outlook%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E73%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20domestic%20passengers%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20data%20by%20the%20trade%20association%20Airlines%20for%20America.%20By%202023%2C%20their%20share%20of%20passengers%20had%20fallen%20to%2052%25%20as%20lower-cost%20airlines%20like%20Southwest%2C%20JetBlue%2C%20Spirit%2C%20and%20Frontier%20emerged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20development%20led%20to%20cheaper%20airfares%20through%20what%20airline%20insiders%20call%20the%20%26quot%3BSouthwest%20Effect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20researchers%20have%20studied%20airfare%2C%20they've%20found%20that%20when%20a%20low-cost%20carrier%20like%20Southwest%20or%20Spirit%20begins%20flying%20a%20new%20route%2C%20fares%20fall%20an%20average%20of%2020%25%20on%20all%20airlines%20operating%20that%20route%2C%26quot%3B%20Keyes%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20because%20price%20is%20by%20far%20the%20most%20important%20factor%20for%20leisure%20travelers'%20purchase%20decision%2C%20and%20so%20competition%20from%20new%20airlines%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20low-cost%20carriers%20%E2%80%94%20drives%20down%20fares%20across%20the%20board.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeyes%20said%20another%20factor%20that%20has%20pushed%20down%20fares%20is%20%26quot%3Bmore%20and%20larger%20airplanes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20having%20more%20planes%20in%20their%20fleets%20than%20they%20used%20to%2C%20airlines%20have%20retired%20smaller%20planes%20in%20recent%20decades%20and%20replaced%20them%20with%20larger%20aircraft.%20In%202005%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airlines.org%2Fdataset%2Fa4a-presentation-industry-review-and-outlook%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E11%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20commercial%20airplanes%20had%20at%20least%20151%20seats%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20to%2048%25%20as%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLarger%20planes%2C%20better%20fuel%20efficiency%2C%20and%20more%20seats%20are%20lowering%20the%20overall%20flight%20costs%20for%20airlines%2C%20and%20those%20savings%20are%20being%20passed%20onto%20travelers%2C%26quot%3B%20Keyes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20competition%20of%20cheaper%20airlines%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20lower%20inflation-adjusted%20fares%20they%20helped%20bring%20about%20%E2%80%94%20airlines%20like%20United%2C%20American%2C%20and%20Delta%20haven't%20suffered%20for%20it%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decline%20in%20inflation-adjusted%20airfares%20appears%20to%20be%20uncorrelated%20with%20the%20financial%20performance%20of%20the%20'big%20three'%20airlines%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeyes%20said%20the%20years%20between%202015%20and%202019%20were%20%26quot%3Bamong%20the%20most%20profitable%20ever%26quot%3B%20for%20US%20airlines.%20He%20said%20declining%20inflation-adjusted%20fares%20haven't%20hindered%20airline%20profits%20because%20their%20business%20models%20aren't%20as%20reliant%20on%20ticket%20revenue%20as%20they%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20airline%20revenue%20comes%20primarily%20from%20sources%20other%20than%20economy%20tickets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20includes%20premium%20cabin%20revenue%2C%20credit%20cards%2C%20business%20travel%2C%20ancillary%20fees%2C%20cargo%2C%20and%20other%20sources.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22286ca0aa-d6de-4865-8a5e-fbb1378a8acf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Americans%20don't%20feel%20like%20they're%20getting%20a%20deal%20on%20airfares%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20airfare%20prices%20are%20more%20affordable%20than%20they%20used%20to%20be%2C%20there%20could%20be%20several%20explanations%20why%20Americans%20remain%20frustrated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumers%20may%20not%20always%20think%20about%20inflation-adjusted%20airfares%2C%20so%20their%20frustration%20could%20be%20due%20to%20the%20higher%20nominal%20level%20of%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20also%20be%20that%20travelers%20are%20more%20frustrated%20by%20their%20travel%20experience%20as%20there's%20been%20a%20slight%20increase%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-delays-newark-forced-passenger-drive-take-flight-find-luggage-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflight%20delays%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20possible%20that%20after%20airfare%20prices%20plummeted%20due%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%202022's%20swift%20rise%20in%20airfares%20caught%20Americans%20off%20guard.%20In%20September%202022%2C%20airfares%20rose%20roughly%2043%25%20compared%20to%20the%20prior%20year%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fpolicy%2Ftransportation%2Faviation%2F3686319-