trict%2C%20and%20over%20the%20next%2014%20months%20I%20lost%20200%20pounds.%20I%20never%20used%20any%20weight%20loss%20drugs%2C%20although%2C%20to%20be%20honest%2C%20I%20was%20a%20bit%20bitter%20that%20they%20became%20available%20only%20a%20few%20months%20after%20I%20was%20done%20losing%20weight!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd6144b5-e7bb-4549-b6e4-f72e227089d8%5C%22%3EI'm%20still%20learning%20about%20moderation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-loss-success-stories-and-tips-2018-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edieting%20success%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20because%20I%20was%20so%20strict.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20of%20moderation%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20all%20or%20nothing.%20But%20as%20I%20reached%20my%20goal%20weight%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20wasn't%20going%20to%20work%20long%20term.%20I%20wanted%20to%20balance%20a%20long%20life%20with%20a%20life%20well%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20a%20beautiful%20day%20and%20I'm%20getting%20coffee%20with%20a%20friend%2C%20I%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20eat%20a%20cookie%20with%20that.%20Later%2C%20if%20I%20stroll%20around%20and%20pass%20an%20ice%20cream%20shop%2C%20I%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stop%20there%2C%20too.%20Joy%20in%20food%20is%20part%20of%20what%20makes%20life%20beautiful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20working%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-stopped-overeating-health-foods-ate-anything-lost-35-pounds-maintained-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elearning%20moderation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20helps%20to%20realize%20that%20my%20relationship%20with%20food%20will%20last%20my%20entire%20life%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bea9eca0-de71-4d78-96ea-ccccb6f3be75%5C%22%3ENo%20amount%20of%20body%20positivity%20would%20save%20me%20from%20bad%20health%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20I%20was%20fat%2C%20and%20so%20was%20my%20sister%20Alisa%2C%20who%20co-authored%20my%20book%20with%20me.%20Our%20mom%20did%20her%20best%2C%20but%20as%20a%20single%20working%20mom%20she%20was%20often%20pulling%20casseroles%20from%20the%20freezer.%20We%20never%20learned%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20eat%20lasagne%20multiple%20times%20each%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20adults%2C%20Alisa%20and%20I%20are%20both%20much%20healthier%20than%20we%20were%20growing%20up%2C%20though%20we're%20still%20fat.%20These%20days%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20talk%20about%20body%20positivity%2C%20almost%20in%20opposition%20to%20weight%20loss.%20I%20hate%20how%20body%20positivity%20can%20be%20used%20to%20sell%20me%20shit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20to%20make%20way%20for%20both%20mindsets.%20I%20can%20love%20my%20(still%20fat)%20body%20while%20also%20making%20it%20as%20healthy%20as%20possible%2C%20which%20might%20involve%20losing%20weight.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20no%20amount%20of%20body%20love%20would%20save%20me%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20was%20slowly%20killing%20myself%20with%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ef4322d9-b525-434b-ac7c-ef594ccdd7a6%5C%22%3EI%20want%20other%20people%20to%20know%20they%20can%20make%20changes%20to%20get%20healthier%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20write%20a%20book%20for%20fat%20people%20by%20a%20fat%20person.%20We're%20often%20handled%20with%20pity%20or%20disgust%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20bring%20empathy%20and%20compassion%20to%20the%20conversation.%20I%20wanted%20to%20share%20a%20story%20from%20two%20people%20who%20have%20felt%20utter%20desperation%20to%20lose%20weight%20and%20who%20have%20managed%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20are%20naturally%20thin%20or%20bookish%20doctors%20who%20have%20never%20had%20to%20work%20at%20losing%20weight%20don't%20realize%20how%20daunting%20the%20prospect%20can%20feel.%20When%20I%20weighed%20420%20pounds%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20climbing%20Mount%20Everest%20would%20have%20seemed%20more%20reasonable%20than%20losing%20200%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20did