th.%20While%20this%20distance%20may%20appear%20considerable%2C%20in%20astronomical%20terms%2C%20it%20qualifies%20as%20a%20close%20approach.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cb%3ENo%20immediate%20threat%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%202024%20KA1%20has%20been%20categorised%20within%20the%20Apollo%20group%20of%20asteroids%2C%20and%20despite%20its%20seemingly%20huge%20size%2C%20experts%20say%20that%20it%20poses%20no%20direct%20threat%20to%20planet%20Earth.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20near-Earth%20objects%20(NEOs)%20do%20not%20pose%20any%20immediate%20danger.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20a%20subset%20of%20asteroids%2C%20known%20as%20potentially%20hazardous%20asteroids%20(PHAs)%2C%20that%20require%20more%20scrutiny.%20PHAs%20are%20defined%20by%20their%20size%2C%20exceeding%20460%20feet%2C%20and%20their%20proximity%20to%20Earth's%20orbit%2C%20approaching%207.5%20million%20km.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnNASA%20and%20its%20global%20network%20of%20observatories%20(such%20as%20Pan-STARRS%20and%20the%20Catalina%20Sky%20Survey)%2C%20including%20both%20professional%20and%20amateur%20astronomers%2C%20continuously%20monitor%20NEOs%2C%20looking%20for%20potential%20risks.%20The%20data%20collected%20from%20these%20observations%20help%20track%20the%20routes%20of%20asteroids%20like%202024%20KA1.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnRadar%20projects%20like%20the%20Goldstone%20Solar%20System%20Radar%20Group%20at%20NASA's%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%20also%20contribute%20invaluable%20insights%20into%20the%20composition%20and%20movement%20of%20NEOs.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cb%3EUpcoming%20asteroids%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOver%20the%20next%20few%20days%2C%20Earth%20will%20witness%20several%20close%20encounters%20with%20asteroids.%20Following%20the%202024%20KA1%2C%20asteroid%202024%20LC%2C%20roughly%2084%20feet%20in%20size%2C%20will%20pass%20by%20at%20a%20distance%20of%20approximately%204%2C703%2C168%20km.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThen%2C%20on%20June%2011%2C%202024%2C%20two%20more%20asteroids%20will%20make%20their%20close%20approaches.%20Asteroid%202024%20LD%2C%20measuring%20about%2067%20feet%2C%20will%20pass%20within%20approximately%204%2C635%2C552%20km%20of%20Earth%20and%20asteroid%202024%20CR9%2C%20with%20an%20approximate%20size%20of%201%2C400%20feet%2C%20will%20come%20within%20about%207%2C371%2C520%20km%20of%20our%20planet.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThese%20encounters%20are%20also%20not%20expected%20to%20pose%20any%20immediate%20threat%20to%20Earth.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717831020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-04%2Fasteroid-generic-istock-650_650x400_41492570432.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmassive-90-foot-asteroid-to-pass-by-earth-today-all-you-need-to-know-5844331%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%2099-foot%20wide%20asteroid%2C%20named%202024%20KA1%2C%20will%20fly%20close%20to%20Earth%20on%20Saturday.%20This%20celestial%20visitor%20is%20travelling%20at%20a%20speed%20of%2029%2C961%20kmph%2C%20and%20will%20make%20its%20closest%20approach%20to%20Earth%20at%2016%3A36%20IST.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmassive-90-foot-asteroid-to-pass-by-earth-today-all-you-need-to-know-5844331%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmassive-90-foot-asteroid-to-pass-by-earth-today-all-you-need-to-know-5844331%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmassive-90-foot-asteroid-to-pass-by-earth-today-all-you-need-to-know-5844331%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22South%20Korea%20on%20alert%20for%20more%20trash%20balloons%20from%20the%20North%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717830960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110815489%2Cimgsize-135486.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatim