3EI%20hoped%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20working%20at%20IBM%20until%20I%20finished%20my%20career%20unless%20another%20great%20opportunity%20presented%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20laid%20off%20in%20September%202015%20when%20I%20was%2055.%20I%20was%20surprised%20when%20my%20boss%20told%20me%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20shocked.%20I'd%20been%20laid%20off%20earlier%20in%20my%20career%20and%20always%20knew%20it%20was%20a%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f4f4a83-b469-4838-a397-12d8f653c3ac%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20been%20laid%20off%20before%20%E2%80%94%20in%20my%2030s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20laid%20off%20at%2031%2C%20only%20three%20months%20after%20joining%20the%20organization%20where%20I%20was%20working.%20I%20had%20two%20kids%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-decided-not-pay-off-mortgage-early-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wasn't%20prepared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20changed%20my%20perspective.%20After%20that%2C%20I%20viewed%20every%20role%20as%20a%20bridge%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20I%20kept%20my%20network%20current%2C%20updated%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresume-mistakes-and-cliches-hiring-managers-are-bored-of-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20twice%20a%20year%2C%20kept%20my%20LinkedIn%20profile%20current%2C%20and%20always%20looked%20for%20other%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20when%20I%20was%20told%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20laid%20off%20from%20IBM%20in%20August%2C%20I%20was%20ready%20for%20it.%20My%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20was%20already%20updated%2C%20and%20I%20started%20applying%20for%20jobs%20on%20my%20way%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279b7b675-3b2a-443a-8f30-65b27976a6c8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20knew%20that%20it%20would%20be%20harder%20the%202nd%20time%20around%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20wasn't%20on%20my%20side.%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20take%20me%20several%20months%20if%20not%20longer%2C%20to%20find%20my%20next%20opportunity.%20I%20knew%20being%20older%2C%20there%20were%20fewer%20opportunities%20because%20I'm%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20there%20are%20fewer%20roles%20where%20the%20hiring%20manager%20is%20looking%20for%20someone%20with%20that%20level%20of%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20laid%20off%20at%2031%2C%20I%20was%20given%20two%20months'%20notice%20in%20October%2C%20and%20by%20February%2C%20I%20had%20landed%20another%20position.%20I%20was%20younger%2C%20cheaper%20and%20the%20job%20market%20was%20probably%20a%20bit%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22617dfdb3-a4bb-44fc-a84e-3d9698635d1e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20a%20kid%20at%20home%20and%20a%20mortgage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%202015%20layoff%2C%20I%20looked%20for%20freelance%20consulting%20work%20because%20I%20needed%20an%20income%20to%20bridge%20the%20gap%20until%20I%20landed%20a%20new%20job.%20My%20third%20child%20was%20still%20living%20at%20home%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20pay%20the%20bills%20and%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20to%20make%20some%20financial%20adjustments%20as%20a%20family.%20I%20thought%20getting%20a%20new%20job%20could%20take%20as%20long%20as%20a%20year.%20We%20paused%20our%20investments%20in%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-turo-car-rental-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efunds%20for%20our%20kid's%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-social-security-magic-number-how-much-money-need-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20increased%20her%20work%20hours%20from%20part-time%20to%20full-time%2C%20and%20because%20of%20that%2C%20we%20were%20both%20able%20to%20enroll%20in%20her%20company's%20health%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20a%20business%20associate%20who%20ran%20a%20small%20marketing%20firm.%20He%20was%20growing%20and%20needed%20people%20to%20work.%20The%20next%20week%2C%20I%20started%20doing%20freelance%20content%20writing%20for%20him.%20Some%20weeks%2C%20I%20worked%2030%20hours%20on%20freelance%20projects%3B%20some%20weeks%2C%20it%20was%2012%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20as%20much%20as%20I%20had%20been%20making%2C%20but%20it%20was%20significant.%20Doing%20something%20kept%20me%20from%20worrying%20about%20my%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eaa61e0b-b21a-46b3-80fd-892d1ebb3e1f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20networked%20to%20find%20job%20opportunities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20treated%20finding%20a%20job%20like%20having%20a%20job.%20I%20applied%20for%2060%20jobs%2C%20spoke%20to%20around%2020%20recruiters%2C%20and%20got%20between%20eight%20and%2012%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquestions-to-ask-in-job-interview-to-get-the-role-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterviews%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20only%20applied%20to%20jobs%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20a%20chance%20of%20getting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20I%20saw%20a%20job%20I%20wanted%2C%20I%20found%20someone%20at%20the%20company%20who%20worked%20in%20that%20function%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-job-search-during-a-recession-networking-email-template-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%20and%20reached%20out%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20could%20help%20slip%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20stack.%20The%20human%20element%20was%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20greatest%20asset%20was%20the%20network%20I'd%20built%20over%20the%20years.%20When%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20people%2C%20they%20told%20me%20about%20job%20opportunities%20in%20their%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20very%20organized.%20I%20kept%20records%20of%20every%20job%20I%20applied%20for%2C%20every%20interaction%20I%20had%2C%20and%20every%20contact%20I%20made%20in%20my%20network%20so%20I%20knew%20when%20to%20follow%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278d69d53-e685-459b-a84b-85fcd40586c9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20experienced%20ageism%20in%20my%20search%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-cant-find-job-retirement-worry-ageism-social-security-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebias%20against%20older%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20some%20interviews%2C%20I%20could%20see%20the%20light%20go%20out%20in%20their%20eyes%20when%20they%20realized%20my%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20one%20job%20I%20didn't%20get%20where%20I%20saw%20the%20person%20they%20ended%20up%20hiring%20was%20much%20younger%20and%20had%20significantly%20less%20experience%20than%20I%20did%20or%20even%20than%20the%20job%20had%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20are%20never%20going%20to%20tell%20you%20it's%20because%20of%20your%20age%2C%20but%20it%20was%20in%20the%20back%20of%20my%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a433cbd-4082-43a3-8275-6a7c8fa29fa4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20landed%20a%20job%20after%206%20months%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20heard%20about%20a%20job%20through%20a%20contact%20in%20my%20network.%20I'd%20applied%20for%20a%20role%20at%20her%20company%20and%20hadn't%20gotten%20it.%20During%20a%20chat%20with%20her%20afterward%2C%20she%20said%20a%20recruiter%20had%20reached%20out%20to%20her%20the%20previous%20week%20with%20a%20role.%20She%20didn't%20want%20it%20because%20she%20wasn't%20looking%20to%20move%20but%20thought%20I'd%20be%20a%20good%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20gave%20the%20recruiter%20my%20name%2C%20and%20I%20landed%20the%20offer%20three%20weeks%20later%2C%20in%20March%202016.%20It%20was%20such%20a%20relief%20to%20have%20a%20salary%20and%20to%20start%20saving%20again%20for%20my%20son's%20college%20fund%20and%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%