%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euntouched%20by%20chemical%20sprays%20or%20insecticides%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20here%20that%20the%20roots%20of%20Doon%20Gooseberry%20Farm%20run%20deep%2C%20where%20our%20dedication%20to%20purity%20and%20quality%20is%20firm.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20use%20shells%20of%20organic%20eggs%2C%20vegetable%20peels%2C%20and%20cow%20manure%20as%20the%20prime%20source%20of%20nourishment%20for%20their%20cultivation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201455px)%20100vw%2C%201455px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FAmla-trees-at-the-farm_11zon-1717158064.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221455%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20amla%20(gooseberry)%20trees%20lining%20the%20farm.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FAmla-trees-at-the-farm_11zon-1717158064.jpg%201455w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FAmla-trees-at-the-farm_11zon-1717158064-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FAmla-trees-at-the-farm_11zon-1717158064-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FAmla-trees-at-the-farm_11zon-1717158064-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FAmla-trees-at-the-farm_11zon-1717158064-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-351732%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221092%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20amla%20(gooseberry)%20trees%20lining%20the%20farm.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20journey%20has%20been%20far%20from%20smooth.%20%E2%80%9CWater%20availability%20is%20a%20critical%20issue%2C%E2%80%9D%20Namita%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBeing%20in%20a%20hilly%20area%20with%20a%20non-perennial%20river%20nearby%2C%20water%20scarcity%20is%20a%20significant%20challenge.%20This%20is%20a%20primary%20reason%20why%20many%20people%20around%20us%20are%20abandoning%20their%20agricultural%20lands.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20create%20canals%20for%20water%20supply%2C%20Namita%20notes%20that%20there%20is%20still%20a%20severe%20shortage%2C%20particularly%20during%20the%20summer%20months.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20currently%20exploring%20rainwater%20harvesting%20as%20a%20potential%20solution%20to%20create%20a%20reliable%20source%20of%20water%2C%E2%80%9D%20Namita%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20we%20sincerely%20hope%20that%20the%20water%20situation%20improves.%20While%20the%20river%20has%20some%20water%20at%20certain%20points%2C%20other%20areas%20remain%20completely%20dry.%20We%20believe%20that%20if%20the%20government%20addresses%20this%20issue%20earnestly%2C%20it%20will%20not%20only%20benefit%20us%20but%20also%20many%20others%20who%20wish%20to%20pursue%20farming%20with%20greater%20ease%20and%20happiness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F298011%2Fgurugram-retired-woman-starts-ayurvedic-veena-jis-hair-oil-business-to-reduce-hair-fall%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDoon%20Gooseberry%20Farm%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecollaborates%20with%20local%20women%20and%20small%20processing%20units%20to%20manufacture%20its%20products.%20However%2C%20the%20farm%20aspires%20to%20establish%20its%20own%20processing%20unit%20staffed%20entirely%20by%20women%20in%20the%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20initiated%20our%20venture%20with%20the%20assistance%20of%20an%20agricultural%20loan%20and%20help%20from%20family%2C%E2%80%9D%20Namita%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20enabled%20us%20to%20make%20the%20land%20cultivable%20and%20fulfill%20our%20basic%20requirements.%20Now%2C%20our%20goal%20is%20to%20expand%20further%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20providing%20employment%20opportunities%20to%20locals%2C%20particularly%20women.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20has%20been%20written%20by%20Shweta%20Bhanot%20Mehrotra.%20Picture%20credits%3A%20Manisha%20and%20Namita.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717158435000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FSisters-pose-at-the-farm-1717157740.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D351707%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20chance%20visit%20to%20Manisha%20Gosain's%20land%20in%20Dehradun%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20gave%20her%20and%20her%20sister%2C%20Namita%20Rawat%20Negi%2C%20the%20idea%20to%20convert%20it%20into%20the%20Doon%20Gooseberry%20Farm.%20They%20grow%20vegetables%20like%20tomatoes%2C%20brinjals%2C%20pumpkins%2C%20spinach%2C%20and%20more%2C%20and%20sell%20value-added%20products%20made%20from%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Guest%20Contributor%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F351707%2Fdoon-gooserberry-farm-dehradun-sisters-amla-farming-growing-mangoes-brinjals-tomatoes-lemons-in-hilly-areas%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%2025%2C%20This%20Agripreneur%20Has%20Converted%202500%20Tons%20of%20Waste%20into%20Vermicompost%20%26amp%3B%20Trained%202500%20Farmers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EYash%20Dayal%20Sharma%20grew%20up%20reading%20the%20books%20of%20Dr%20A%20P%20J%20Abdul%20Kalam%2C%20developing%20a%20strong%20desire%20to%20serve%20the%20nation.%20When%20his%20first%20choice%2C%20a%20career%20in%20the%20armed%20forces%20didn%E2%80%99t%20materialise%2C%20he%20shifted%20his%20vision%20to%20agriculture.%20Hailing%20from%20a%20family%20of%20farmers%20in%20Saharanpur%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20research%20during%20his%20college%20days%20revealed%20that%20one%20of%20the%20major%20problems%20that%20our%20country%20faces%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331849%2Fgardening-dr-navdeep-singh-khurana-dentist-amritsar-flowers-vegetables-indoor-garden%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoil%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20to%20several%20lands%20becoming%20uncultivable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20FAO%20(Food%20and%20Agriculture%20Organization)%20and%20UNCCD%20(United%20Nations%20Convention%20to%20Combat%20Desertification)%20Global%20Outlook%20report%20states%20that%20over%2029%20percent%20(96.4%20million%20hectares)%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20agricultural%20land%20is%20degraded%2C%20wherein%20the%20land%20has%20lost%20its%20top%20soil.%20This%20is%20a%20worrying%20trend%20as%20the%20Indian%20population%20is%20increasing%20at%20a%20rapid%20pace%2C%20while%20cultivable%20land%20is%20decreasing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELearning%20about%20this%20alarming%20fact%20made%20the%2025-year-old%20return%20to%20his%20roots%20in%20Saharanpur%20to%20first%20understand%20the%20problems%20in%20the%20agricultural%20sector%20and%20look%20at%20possible%20solutions.%20From%202020%20to%202021%2C%20armed%20with%20a%20certification%20in%20organic%20farming%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%2C%20he%20interacted%20with%20farmers%2C%20scientists%2C%20and%20other%20stakeholders%20to%20understand%20the%20root%20causes%20of%20soil%20degradation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20firm%20understanding%20that%20soil%20health%20had%20to%20be%20improved%2C%20a%20deep%20dive%20into%20the%20topic%20led%20to%20the%20understanding%20that%20the%20solution%20was%20staring%20right%20in%20his%20face%20the%20entire%20time%20%E2%80%94%20the%20earthworm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20earthworm%20that%20decomposes%20organic%20waste%20into%20vermicompost.Starting%20with%20a%20trial%20batch%20of%20vermicompost%20on%20one%20acre%20of%20his%20farm%2C%20he%20founded%20Fertile%20Beeghas%20in%20June%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%20the%20enterprise%20has%20transformed%20over%202%2C500%20tonnes%20of%20cattle%20dung%20and%20organic%20waste%20into%20vermicompost.%20Yash%20shares%20he%20has%20also%20provided%20training%20to%20over%202%2C500%20farmers%20in%20organic%20farming%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20how%20he%20plans%20to%20improve%20the%20soil%20fertility%20of%20degraded%20soils.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Treat%20soil%20as%20a%20living%20entity%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYash%20always%20harboured%20a%20vision%20to%20create%20a%20better%20India.%20While%20pursuing%20his%20BA%20in%20history%20from%20Delhi%20University%2C%20he%20started%20a%20school%20for%20underprivileged%20children%20called%20%E2%80%98Free%20School%20Under%20The%20Mowgli%20Tree%E2%80%99.%20Here%2C%20he%20encouraged%20children%20to%20think%20out%20of%20the%20box%20and%20develop%20practical%20skills%20as%20most%20of%20them%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20access%20to%20a%20formal%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC4NqJz7yjS_%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC4NqJz7yjS_%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC4NqJz7yjS_%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Fertile%20Beeghas%20%7C%20Organic%20Farms%20%7C%20Vermicomposting%20(%40fertilebeeghas)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20imposition%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20lockdown%20brought%20a%20halt%20to%20the%20school%20and%20led%20to%20Yash%20contemplating%20his%20future%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20great-grandfather%20and%20grandfather%20were%20farmers.%20I%20grew%20up%20close%20to%20nature%20in%20a%20boarding%20school%20in%20Pune.%20When%20I%20was%20considering%20what%20path%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20after%20my%20graduation%2C%20I%20chose%20agriculture%20as%20this%20sector%20needs%20a%20lot%20of%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20Yash%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20reason%20for%20choosing%20agriculture%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F299979%2Fbooks-loved-and-recommended-by-apj-abdul-kalam-fiction-science-spirituality%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr%20A%20P%20J%20Abdul%20Kalam%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20former%20president%20stressed%20his%20vision%202020%20for%20the%20nation.%20Although%20he%20had%20written%20these%20books%20decades%20ago%2C%20Yash%20realised%20that%20we%20are%20far%20from%20reaching%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDr%20Kalam%20spoke%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20youth%20and%20how%20we%20should%20contribute%20to%20the%20betterment%20of%20the%20nation.%20Inspired%20by%20him%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20do%20something%20good%20for%20the%20country%20by%20focusing%20on%20agriculture%20and%20improving%20the%20lives%20of%20farmers%20as%20well%20as%20agricultural%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20reiterates%20Yash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20started%20visiting%20farmers%20in%20Saharanpur%2C%20he%20was%20appalled%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98cocktail%20of%20pesticides%E2%80%99%20being%20used%20in%20their%20farmlands.%20Constant%20use%20of%20pesticides%20also%20has%20a%20detrimental%20effect%20on%20soil%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20National%20Rainfed%20Area%20Authority%20(NRAA)%20CEO%20Ashok%20Dalwai%20said%20that%20the%20Soil%20Organic%20Carbon%20(SOC)%20content%20in%20India%20had%20come%20down%20to%200.3%20percent%20from%20one%20percent%20in%20the%20past%2070%20years.%20SOC%20is%20one%20of%20the%20major%20indicators%20of%20robust%20soil%20and%20gives%20soil%20its%20fertility%2C%20water-retention%20capacity%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSoil%20is%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20most%20of%20our%20problems.%20While%20healthy%20soil%20should%20have%20at%20least%20five%20to%2010%20percent%20SOC%2C%20the%20benchmark%20in%20India%20is%20one%20percent.%20As%20the%20statistics%20show%2C%20our%20farms%20have%20less%20than%200.5%20percent.%20I%20was%20shocked%20by%20this%3B%20visiting%20farms%20in%20Saharanpur%20was%20an%20eye-opener%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20many%20documentaries%2C%20read%20books%20and%20met%20stakeholders.%20I%20compared%20the%20soil%20status%20of%20farmlands%20in%20Western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Haryana%20with%20soil%20samples%20from%20Europe.%20The%20results%20were%20shocking%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Yash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnless%20steps%20are%20taken%20to%20improve%20the%20SOC%20and%20fertility%20of%20the%20soil%2C%20in%20a%20few%20years%20it%20will%20also%20become%20non-arable.%20Realising%20this%2C%20he%20met%20farmers%2C%20producers%2C%20microbiologists%2C%20Government%20officials%2C%20and%20scientists%20over%20a%20year%20to%20understand%20the%20possible%20solutions%20to%20improve%20soil%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECharles%20Darwin%20published%20the%20solution%20several%20centuries%20ago%20in%20his%20book%20%E2%80%98The%20Formation%20of%20Vegetable%20Mould%2C%20through%20the%20Actions%20of%20Worms%E2%80%99.%20%E2%80%9CEarthworms%20improve%20the%20physical%2C%20chemical%20and%20biological%20properties%20of%20soil.%20They%20are%20a%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20best%20friend%20and%20no%20fertiliser%20works%20quite%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F348522%2Fvermicompost-made-by-award-winning-kashmir-organic-farmer-anantnag-units-earns-crores%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evermicompost%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Yash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYash%20then%20went%20in%20search%20of%20vermicompost.%20Unsatisfied%20with%20the%20ones%20he%20found%20in%20the%20market%2C%20he%20developed%20one%20following%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20best%20scientific%20practices%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202021%20to%202022%2C%20he%20worked%20on%20making%20vermicompost%20on%20one%20acre%20of%20his%20own%20land%20in%20Saharanpur.%20He%20distributed%20samples%20in%20nearby%20farmlands%2C%20and%20once%20he%20was%20satisfied%20with%20the%20results%2C%20he%20started%20selling%20them%20through%20his%20company%20Fertile%20Beeghas%20in%20October%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20different%20about%20his%20vermicompost%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYash%20states%20that%20what%20differentiates%20his%20vermicompost%20is%20the%20manufacturing%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2Ffertile-beeghas2-1717155322.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vermicompost%20being%20prepared%20at%20Fertile%20Beeghas%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2F